  <body>
    <div class="example" id="aws-configure">
      <h2><a href="./">AWS by Example</a>: AWS Configure</h2>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>All interactions with AWS require creating and using &ldquo;Access Keys&rdquo;.</p>

<p>We can create &ldquo;root&rdquo; access keys on the
<a href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/iam/home?region=us-east-1#security_credential">&ldquo;Security Credentials&rdquo; dashboard</a>.</p>

<p>Click &ldquo;Continue to Security Credentials&rdquo;, &ldquo;Access Keys (Access Key ID and Secret Access Key)&rdquo;,
&ldquo;Create New Access Key&rdquo;, and &ldquo;Show Access Key&rdquo;.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code empty">
            
          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>To interact with AWS via the Command Line Interface
(CLI), configure credentials with <code>aws configure</code></p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="gp">$</span> aws configure
<span class="go">AWS Access Key ID [None]: &lt;Paste Access Key ID&gt;</span>
<span class="go">AWS Secret Access Key [None]: &lt;Paste Secret Access Key&gt;</span>
<span class="go">Default region name [None]: us-east-1</span>
<span class="go">Default output format [None]: json</span>
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Credentials are stored in our home directory:</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="gp">$</span> cat ~/.aws/config
<span class="go">[default]</span>
<span class="go">aws_access_key_id = AKIA...</span>
<span class="go">aws_secret_access_key = SFoH...</span>
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>We can then manage AWS resources with the CLI.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="gp">$</span> aws ec2 describe-instances
<span class="go">{</span>
<span class="go">    &quot;Reservations&quot;: []</span>
<span class="go">}</span>
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Now that we can interact with the AWS APIs with the
CLI, let&rsquo;s learn more about the numerous infrastructure
services.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code empty">
            
          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
      
